-- Finance Ministry Sells One-Year China Bonds at Yield of 1.87%, Traders Say
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-14T02:41:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/finance-ministry-sells-one-year-china-bonds-at-yield-of-1-87-traders-say.html

          
          
             China’s finance ministry sold 28
billion yuan ($4.1 billion) in one-year bonds at an average
yield of 1.87 percent, according to traders at China Citic Bank
Corp. and Industrial Bank Co.  
 The highest winning-bid yield at the sale was 1.91 percent,
said the traders at the primary dealers required to bid at the
government auctions.  
 The average yield at today’s auction was 6 basis points
lower than the 1.93 percent median estimate in a Bloomberg News
survey of 13 finance companies. A basis point is 0.01 percentage
point.  
